subSubSection.paragraph:
Summarizing data from the literature, along with the specimens we examined, 

C. scopaeum

appears to be seasonally polyestrous. Pregnancies occurred in January (
Sinaloa
), February (
Jalisco
), and June (
Jalisco
and 
Nayarit
) (

Jones 
et al.
1972

; 

Watkins 
et al.
1972

). Lactating females have been found in May (
Morelos
) and June (
Nayarit
and 
Jalisco
) (

Watkins 
et al.
1972

). Females noted as non-reproductive were recorded in July (
Chihuahua
; 
Anderson 1972
) and August (
Colima
; 
Wilson 1979
).
